2 unit Beyond Meat®
170 g Spaghetti
113 g Mirepoix
56 g Spring Mix
7 g Thyme
½ cup Marinara Sauce
56 mL Cream
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
1 tbsp Chicken Stock Powder
1 tbsp Red Wine Vinegar
½ tsp Sugar*
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
0.13 tsp Salt*
2 tbsp Unsalted Butter*

Strip thyme leaves from stems, then roughly chop.
Add vinegar, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) sugar and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to a large bowl. Stir to combine. Add spring mix. Do not mix until step 5.

Add spaghetti to the boiling water. Cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender, 10-12 min.
Reserve 1/2 cup (1 cup) pasta water.
When pasta is done, drain and return spaghetti to the same pot, off heat.

Meanwhile, heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) butter, then mirepoix, Beyond Meat® patties and thyme. Season with salt and pepper.
Cook, breaking up patties into small pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.**

Add marinara sauce, stock powder, cream and 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) reserved pasta water to the pan with Beyond Meat®.
Bring to a boil.
Once boiling, reduce heat to medium-low. Cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce thickens slightly, 4-5 min.

Add Beyond Meat® bolognese sauce to the pot with spaghetti, then toss to coat. ( TIP: For a lighter sauce consistency, add more reserved pasta water, 1-2 tbsp at a time, if desired.)
Toss salad.
Divide spaghetti bolognese and salad between plates.
Sprinkle Parmesan over top.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, cook and plate it the same way as the pork, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.**